BugReports: https://github.com/optimal2050/energyRt/issues
Description: A macro-language for energy system modeling in R. Describe an
    energy system as R objects (commodities, technologies, supply, demand,
    storage, trade), compile it into a capacity-expansion and dispatch
    optimization model, solve it on one of four interchangeable backends
    (GLPK/MathProg, Julia/JuMP, Python/Pyomo, or GAMS), and analyze tidy
    results with built-in tools for levelized costs, technology reports,
    and plotting.
Depends: R (>= 4.3)
